FBIS3-16394 "drsov051_t_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-051 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Mar 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Government Submits Bill Outlining State Secrets WS1503205394 Tallinn ETA in English 1916 GMT 15 Mar 94 WS1503205394 Tallinn ETA Language: English Article Type:BFN ["News Release"] [Text] Tallinn, March 15 -- Estonian Government, on Tuesday [15 March], sent law on state secrets, defining the regulations on pieces of information, declared a state secret, to the Riigikogu [parliament], Minister of Justice Kaido Kama told a press conference. Kama said that the bill defines also areas on which information cannot be concealed e.g. information on emergency cases, nature catastrophes, information concerning ecological and demographic situation. Government will appoint an expert working group that will propose which information to consider a state secret. If the proposition is adopted, defence of the secrets will be carried out by the Defence Police Department.
